@page "/"

<PageTitle>LinkedIn Post Generator</PageTitle>

<div class="container-fluid mt-4">
    <div class="row mb-4">
        <div class="col-12 text-center">
            <h2 class="display-5">LinkedIn Post Generator</h2>
            <p class="text-muted">
                Fill in your topic, role, and audience — your author profile does the rest.
                Posts are generated in your voice and adjusted to your target length.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-12">
            <PostGeneratorWidget />
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row mt-5">
        <div class="col-12">
            <div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
                <h5 class="alert-heading"><i class="bi bi-info-circle me-2"></i>About This Demo</h5>
                <p class="mb-0">
                    This pipeline runs two sequential stages: <strong>post generation</strong> — the LLM drafts an
                    engaging post using your topic, role, audience, and author profile as context; and
                    <strong>length adjustment</strong> — a second LLM pass shortens or preserves the draft to hit your
                    target character count. Your author profile (bio, writing guidelines, and previous post references)
                    is loaded from <code>profile.json</code> and injected as the system prompt for every generation.
                    Update it any time on the <a href="profile">My Profile</a> page.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
